cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO

This paper is about developing an intelligent agent to play a physics-based puzzle game, which requires reasoning and prediction with limited environmental information. This involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and robotics (cs.RO). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, followed by cs.GT and cs.LG. The use of computer vision and robotics is less emphasized, but still relevant, hence cs.CV and cs.RO are also possible sub-categories.
